        followup: "This reveals GRADE's limitation: certainty ratings inform decisions but don't make them. Surgeons argued: 'My patients improve.' Patients wanted the procedure. Systems had invested in it. A HIGH certainty of 'no benefit' should have ended the practice—but implementation requires more than evidence rating. GRADE tells us what the evidence says; behavior change requires understanding why evidence gets ignored."
